    {
      "id": "PopularPost226401",
      "post_content": "More like \"Irritation\". In a release draft, I got passed 2 of these dead last. Since I was short on my main colors (red/green) I had to put in 3... thinking my werewolves would get some decent use out of them, this didn't seem too bad...\n  \n   \nI was wrong. I got 1 every single game, and although once it saved my arse and won me a match, the rest of the time it was just dead weight. In my very last match, I had one in my opening hand, 1 for my turn two draw, and drew the third the following turn. Even with 3 of these equipped, my opponent was hardly scared. CARD DESIGN FAIL.\n  \n   \nEDIT: I did have some fun when I declared I was \"triple hooding that S\\*\\*\\*!\" and equipped all 3 hoods on a creature. That at least got a laugh. But still, no one was scared. False advertising. 1/5",
      "posted_by": "Entropic_Acolyte",
